SENT.plain: Five patients with internal carotid artery occlusion were studied with MR imaging at 0.22 T
At the carotid siphon, occluded vessels showed absence of flow void in three patients
But two cases had "partial flow void" which mimicked small arterial caliber
In these patients angiography showed collateral circulation to the carotid siphon
So the partial flow void in the carotid siphon suggested internal carotid artery occlusion with collateral circulation
